Movie: The Adventures of Buckaroo Banzai Across the 8th Dimension
Tales from the Crypt: Demon Knight

Review: There's comparisons to be made to Carnival of Souls, sure, but I felt like this film was a bit closer to Dementia (1955) in its execution. Despite some flaws (that soundtrack!), the film's limitations create an intimate feeling through imperfectly framed close-ups and occasional handheld shots. Chalk this one up as another authentic perspective on the relationship between physical and mental dilapidation in twentieth century America, right there with Malatesta’s Carnival of Blood and The Texas Chainsaw Massacre.

Movie: The Hitman Blood Smells Like Rose
Review: Starring a celebrity best known for singing a best-selling Japanese version of “Y.M.C.A.”, this late-period Ishii flick is a revenge-thriller with some dashes of comic humor, a streak of sentimentality, and a few WTF moments up its sleeve. Despite the positives, the film has its flaws, such as the by-the-numbers plotting and a surprising lack of action scenes. Tetsurô Tanba is the MVP in this one, playing a cop that seems to be going the extra mile when it comes…
